Editor's Corner             by @{"Lori Vinciguerra" link P6}


Welcome back to school everyone.  I am hoping that over the summer, many of
you have figured out how to get on the World Wide Web.  It is very exciting
now that many schools are creating web pages.  Hopefully, Ralph's article
in the last issue of the AEL newsletter helped some of you get on the Web.
This issue includes an article about some web sites which may be of
interest to educators. If anyone else has a site to be mentioned, let me
know and I will include it in the next issue.

I have had several people interested in writing an article for the AEL
newsletter. However, there have been questions about what may be of general
interest to all of you.  If you have a suggestion for an article, let me
know.  I may be able to find someone to write about your topic. I think
that any article about what you are doing with your Amiga in the
educational field would be of interest.  I would encourage people to submit
an article for the next issue. The deadline for article submissions for the
next issue is December 1, 1996. As always, email your article to
owl@davinci.reading.ma.us or use U.S. mail to send to OWL Software, 460
Summer Ave., Reading, MA 01867-3819.


